<p>
<seg id=1> Near the city of Bangdanbade in Bihar in eastern India, a train and a bus struck each other at a railway crossing, killing ten people and injuring five. </seg>
<seg id=2> A report by the Press Trust of India said that railway officials held a passenger on the bus responsible for the accident. </seg>
<seg id=3> The report said that a passenger in a hurry seized the key from a guard at the barrier and opened the barrier. </seg>
<seg id=4> But before the bus could cross the tracks, the train was already there. The train and the bus crashed into each other. </seg>
<seg id=5> The dead and injured were all passengers in the bus. </seg>
</p>
